briefdescription.para: Implementation of the Linear Elasticity material model.

detaileddescription.para: \[ \psi(\Bvep) = \frac{\lambda}{2} (\tr \Bvep)^2 +\mu \tr (\Bvep^2) ,\] where $ \Bvep $ denotes the linear strain tensor.
The second Piola-Kirchhoff stresses are computed as \[ \BS(\Bvep) =\fracpt{\psi(\Bvep)}{\Bvep} = \lambda \tr \Bvep \BI +2 \mu \Bvep,\]

and the material tangent moduli are computed as \[ \BBC(\Bvep) =\fracpt{^2\psi(\Bvep)}{\Bvep^2} = \lambda \tr \Bvep \CI +2 \mu \CI^{\mathrm{sym}},\] where $ \CI_{IJKL} = \de_{IJ}\de_{KL}$ and $ \CI_{IJKL}^\mathrm{sym} = \frac{1}{2}(\de_{IK}\de_{JL}+ \de_{IL}\de_{JK})$.
ScalarType_
The scalar type used in the material.
